<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="200" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1455,1589]" pageId="13" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1455,1480]" pageId="13" pageNumber="200">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This monotypic group can be easily recognized by (
<number box="[863,875,1456,1480]" pageId="13" pageNumber="200" value="1.0">1</number>
) two tibial apophyses, (
<number box="[1146,1161,1456,1480]" pageId="13" pageNumber="200" value="2.0">2</number>
) the dorsal lobe of tibia, (
<number box="[160,174,1492,1516]" pageId="13" pageNumber="200" value="3.0">3</number>
) the short septum of epigyne, (
<number box="[539,554,1492,1516]" pageId="13" pageNumber="200" value="4.0">4</number>
) very small receptacles and (
<number box="[894,909,1492,1516]" pageId="13" pageNumber="200" value="4.0">4</number>
) arch-like thin insemination ducts (lacking in other congeners).
</paragraph>
